<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued March 18 at 7:27AM CDT until March 18 at 8:00AM CDT by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 800 AM CDT
FOR NORTH CENTRAL CLARKE AND WILCOX COUNTIES...
At 726 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Potter Station to Thomasville, moving east at 45
mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Thomasville, Camden, Pine Hill and Yellow Bluff.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for southwestern
Alabama.
For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
